##**LAYOUT**
1. Controlling the position of elements
2. Creating site layouts
3. Designing for different sized screens.

. <div> eleemtns are often used as containing elements to group together sections of a page.
. *Browsers* display pages in normal flow unless you specify relative, absolute, or fixed positioning.
. Designers keep pages within 960-1000 pixels wide.

1. Grids help create professional and flexible designs.
2. CSS Frameworks provide rules for common tasks
3. The float property moves content to the left or right of the page and can be used in multi-column.
